    <title type="html"><![CDATA[disable Pure-ftpd logging on syslog]]></title>
    <link href="http://zekus.github.io/blog/2010/02/06/disable-pure-ftpd-logging-on-syslog/"/>
    <updated>2010-02-06T14:33:04+01:00</updated>
    <id>http://zekus.github.io/blog/2010/02/06/disable-pure-ftpd-logging-on-syslog</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>Pure-ftpd is a bit tricky to configure because do not handle the configuration like any other daemon in Linux so you will not find any /etc/pure-ftpd.conf.</p>

<p>According to the pure-ftpd documentation, you should start the daemon already with the options you need. The default Ubuntu installation, use the files in /etc/pure-ftpd/conf/ to set the options for the startup script of pure-ftpd so, to disable the logging, execute the following command in your shell and restart the daemon</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>$ echo "none" &gt; /etc/pure-ftpd/conf/SyslogFacility
</span><span class='line'>$ /etc/init.d/pure-ftpd-mysql restart</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>;)</p>
]]></content>
